#plot the probability of success and fails

plt.scatter(data.hours, data.success, label = 'Data')

plt.xlabel('Hours of Study', fontsize = 15)
plt.ylabel('Pass/Fail', fontsize = 15)
plt.show()

so, the probability of success increased as we make the hours of study greater and probability of fails decreased as we add the hours of study, and vice versa.

In [472]:
#create lag to variable to create lag price data
lags = 5

#create list for store the name of lag
cols = []

#iterate to create lag varible and store the name in a list
#range doesnt including a stop which 5 so we add +1
for lag in range(1, lags + 1):
  col = 'lag{}'.format(lag)
  data[col] = data.returns.shift(lag)
  cols.append(col)
#droping missing values of lag etc
data.dropna(inplace = True)
data

In-Sample Backtesting and the Look-ahead-bias¶

#create strategy returns
data['strategy'] = data.pred * data.returns
In [488]:
#create cumulative return banckmark and strategy return
data['creturns'] = data.returns.cumsum().apply(np.exp)
data['cstrategy'] = data.strategy.cumsum().apply(np.exp)
